'''''A Dictionary of Christian Biography and Literature to the End of the Sixth Century A.D., with an Account of the Principal Sects and Heresies''''' is a 1911 religious encyclopedia of biographies.

Edited by [[William C. Piercy]] and [[Henry Wace (Anglican priest)|Henry Wace]], [[Dean of Canterbury]] (1836–1924) in English-language version, it is in the [[public domain]] {{as of|2004|lc=y}}. The [[Christian Classics Ethereal Library]] has scanned the original printed copy.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ccel.org/w/wace/biodict/ |title=''A Dictionary of Early Christian Biography and Literature to the End of the Sixth Century A.D., with an account of the Principal Sects and Heresies'' |publisher=[http://www.ccel.org/ Christian Classics Ethereal library]}}</ref> In 1999, [[Hendrickson Publishers]] reprinted it under the title ''A Dictionary of Early Christian Biography''.<ref>{{Cite book|title=A Dictionary of Early Christian Biography And Literature to the End of the Sixth Century A.D., with an Account of the Principal Sects and Heresies |publisher=Hendrickson Publishers |location=Peabody |url=http://www.ntslibrary.com/PDF%20Books/Henry%20Wace%20Christian%20Bio%20&%20Lit%206th%20Century.pdf |isbn=1-56563-460-8}}</ref>

Its predecessor was ''A Dictionary of Christian Biography, Literature, Sects and Doctrines'' (four volumes, 1877–87) edited by Wace and [[William Smith (lexicographer)|William Smith]].<ref>{{Cite book|title=A Dictionary of Christian Biography, Literature, Sects and Doctrines |publisher=John Murray, Albemarle Street |location=London |url=http://onlinebooks.library.upenn.edu/webbin/book/lookupid?key=olbp34349}}</ref> That in turn represented an updated version of ''[[Smith's Bible Dictionary]]'' of 1863.

